All Classes

Class Description
AbstractChap
An Actor is a game character that moves around, like Chap, the hero of the game.
AbstractTile
Superclass of Tiles that make up the maze.
AppWindow
The Class AppWindow.
ArrayConvertor
Static helper methods for converting arrays and lists.
Board
The Board class is responsible for representing and maintaining the state of the game, such as what type of objects are on the maze, where they are, whether the level is finished and which actions are allowed to change the state of those objects, etc...
BoardObjectsToSave
For PERSISTENCY to use when saving game To avoid calling multiple methods in Board from the Persistency module.
ClosingOptionPane
Panel for the closing screen.
Countdown
The Class Countdown.
Direction
Enumerates which directions we can travel from current position.
DomainTest
To ensure game logic is sound.
ExitLockTile
The Exit Lock tile blocks the sole entrance into the ExitTile at the beginning of each level.
ExitTile
Once (Regular)Chap reaches this tile, the current game level is won.
ExtraTile
Invented tile that gives (Regular)Chap extra 10 seconds on the countdown clock if he reaches it.
FreeTile
Actors(Regular and Variant) can freely move onto these tiles and nothing would happen.
FuzzTest
To ensure game logic is sound.
Game
The Game class handles the clock and interacts with the App module.
GamePane
The Class GamePane.
GameRenderer
GameRenderer JPanel to display a 2D representation of the maze.
HelpFrame
The frame for the help dropdown menu.
InfoTile
Like a free tile, but when Chap steps on this field, a help text will be displayed.
InventoryRenderer
InventoryRenderer JPanel to display the keys currently held by the player.
KeyDoorColour
Enumerates KeyTile and LockedDoorTile's colours.
KeyTile
Actors can move onto those tiles.
LoadGame
An object used to load a saved game.
LoadGameTests
The Class LoadGameTests.
LockedDoorTile
A Locked Door Tile: Chap can only move onto these tiles if they have the key with the matching colour -- this unlocks the tile.
Main
GUI/Main class for Chap's Challenge.
MenuBar
The Class MenuBar.
MenuPane
The Class MenuPane.
Position
Position of Actor or Tile on board.
Recorder
The Class Recorder.
RegularChap
Chap can be moved by key strokes (up-right-down-left), his movement is restricted by the nature of the tiles (for instance, cannot move into walls).
RendererImages
Stores images to be used in the Renderer module.
RendererSounds
Plays sounds for a GameRenderer.
ReplayPane
The Class ReplayPane.
SaveGame
An object used to save a game.
SaveGameTests
The Class SaveGameTests.
SaveState
The Class SaveState.
TreasureTile
If Chap steps onto this tile, the treasure (chip) is picked up and added to the treasure chest.
VariantChap
The secondary actor used in level 2.
WallTile
Part of a wall, actors can never move onto these tiles.
